## On Failure — Check App Logs

For staging:
```powershell
databricks apps logs hertz-leo-lms-staging --profile DanSiaoAuth --tail-lines 200
```

For prod:
```powershell
databricks apps logs hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem --profile DanSiaoAuth --tail-lines 200
```

Filter for errors:
```powershell
databricks apps logs hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem --profile DanSiaoAuth --tail-lines 500 --search "ERROR"
```

Stream in real time:
```powershell
databricks apps logs hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem --profile DanSiaoAuth --follow
```

- Look for `[APP]` lines: Python tracebacks or startup errors
- Look for `[SYSTEM]` lines: build failures (npm/pip install, vite build)

Report relevant error lines before attempting a fix.

## Rollback

The previous deployment remains active until the new one succeeds. If a prod deploy fails, staging still holds the last known-good state. Fix forward — do not run destructive schema operations to roll back.
